# Astro Conventions

## Project Structure

```
src/
├── pages/              # File-based routing
│   ├── index.astro     # Home page (/)
│   └── about.astro     # /about
├── layouts/
│   └── Layout.astro    # Shared layout
├── components/         # Reusable components (.astro, .tsx, .svelte, .vue)
├── content/            # Content collections (markdown, MDX)
└── styles/             # Global styles
```

## Pages and Routing

File-based routing in `src/pages/`:
- `index.astro` → `/`
- `about.astro` → `/about`
- `posts/[slug].astro` → `/posts/:slug`

## Component Pattern

```astro
---
// Frontmatter: runs at build time (server-side)
const { title } = Astro.props;
const data = await fetch("https://api.example.com/data").then(r => r.json());
---

<!-- Template: HTML + expressions -->
<article>
  <h1>{title}</h1>
  <ul>
    {data.map(item => <li>{item.name}</li>)}
  </ul>
</article>
```

## Layouts

```astro
---
// src/layouts/Layout.astro
const { title } = Astro.props;
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <title>{title}</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <slot />
  </body>
</html>
```

Use layouts in pages:
```astro
---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Home">
  <h1>Welcome</h1>
</Layout>
```

## Islands Architecture

Use `client:*` directives for interactive components:
```astro
<!-- Static by default -->
<StaticComponent />

<!-- Hydrate on page load -->
<Counter client:load />

<!-- Hydrate when visible -->
<LazyChart client:visible />

<!-- Hydrate on idle -->
<Analytics client:idle />
```
